-- Greek New Democracy Leader Samaras Pledges Lower Tax Rates
-- B y   E l e n i   C h r e p a   a n d   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 2012-06-15T09:29:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-15/greek-new-democracy-leader-samaras-pledges-lower-tax-rates.html
The following are the main election
pledges and economic policy of New Democracy leader Antonis Samaras, who is leading in polls ahead of the Greek general
election on June 17.  -- Restore lower pension and benefits for large families to 2009
levels, refund individual bondholders and social security funds
for losses arising from the writedown on holdings of Greek
government debt  -- Pay unemployment benefit for two years instead of one  -- Extend unemployment benefit to the self-employed  -- Cap payment of special taxes at 25 percent of average
 household income   -- Freeze private-sector wages pending new labor agreements  -- Raise the tax threshold from the current 5,000 euros to 8,000
in 2013 and 10,000 in 2014  -- Introduce new property tax and withdraw the current levy
collected via electricity bills  -- Cut tax rates for businesses to 15 percent from 2013,  sales
tax  for restaurants to 9 percent from 23 percent and the maximum
personal income tax rate to 32 percent from 45 percent.  -- Extend program of public spending cuts amounting to 11.7
billion euros to 2016 at least  -- Transfer redundant civil servants to a special labor reserve,
rather than dismiss them  -- Ensure mortgage repayments arenâ€™t more than 30 percent of
monthly income  -- Raise borrowing limits for people rated as high credit risk
in the past two years  -- Inject cash into the market through a liquidity mechanism for
small and medium-sized businesses  -- Commit the state to paying money it owes  -- Scrap bureaucratic restrictions on state properties so they
can be exploited  -- Push forward privatization plans  -- Restore a sense of safety for Greek citizens  -- Declare exclusive maritime economic zones for locating and
exploiting potential offshore oil and natural gas  To contact the reporters on this story:
